The paper deals with adjacency labelling schemes for planar graphs, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The results also generalize to other families of graphs, such as bounded genus graphs and apex-minor-free graphs, which are topics in graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the use of probabilistic methods and random graphs, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
